The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Italian firm to make bike parts
                                                                                                               Italian firm to make bike parts
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, April 10: Italian two-wheeler parts manufacturer Verlicchi has formed a 50:50 joint venture with component supplier Hema group to manufacture motorcycle frames, fuel tanks and exhaust systems. This is the companys first project in the country.         
	The joint venture  Verlicchi Hema Automotive Company  will set up its first facility at Hosur near Bangalore at an investment of Rs 17 crore. The companies plan to set up three units at an investment of approximately Rs 60 crore.         
	India produces only 70 lakh motorcycles annually compared with 2.5 crore in China. But it has great potential, said Alessandro Verlicchi, group managing director of Verlicchi. The joint venture is considering locations such as Pune and Manesar for the units.                                                                                                                                        
